@gridironborn Thanks to a tutorial from @tejfbanalytics I wanted to re-create your graph using EPA values. 

That super outlier is actually not the Browns / Bears game, but the 2019 Bears / Saints game where they rushed for 17 yards on 7 carries. 

#nflverse https://t.co/x7ga710UIV

Catch Rate Over Expected (CROE) through three weeks. We have a new leader: Courtland Sutton.

Confirmed still good at football.

@nflfastR #NFLverse https://t.co/4pmavxsjBJ

#Steelers and #Texans fans should cover their eyes. 

Using data from the #nflverse, here is a look at the percentage of times a team's air yards were &gt;= the yards needed on fourth down. 

